# Line endings are decided here, not by each clone's core.autocrlf.
#
# Without this file the behaviour depends on a local Git setting: a tool that writes LF (sed,
# a script, an editor on another machine) makes Git announce "LF will be replaced by CRLF the
# next time Git touches it", and whether that is even a problem varies per developer.
#
# Text is stored as LF in the repository and checked out as CRLF. That matches .editorconfig
# (end_of_line = crlf) and the Windows-only target — net10.0-windows / WPF, CI on windows-latest
# — so eol=crlf is deliberate rather than platform-dependent: a clone on any OS gets CRLF.
* text=auto eol=crlf

# Shell scripts must keep LF or they fail to run, including under Git Bash on Windows.
*.sh text eol=lf

# Better hunk headers: Git shows the enclosing type/method instead of a random brace.
*.cs diff=csharp

# Binaries — never normalised, never diffed as text. .svg is intentionally absent: it is XML,
# and the brand masters under docs/brand/ are worth diffing.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.ttf binary
*.otf binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.dll binary
*.exe binary
*.pdb binary
*.snk binary
